703759f-a.title: Brooklyn: Columbia Street - Halleck Street
703759f-a.text:
Columbia Street, east side, south of Halleck (left) Street, showing
at the right background the New York State Canal Terminal Building.
The two one story frame shacks at each end are numbered 597 and 601.
Halleck Street appears prominently in the foreground.
August 31, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

703760f-a.title: Brooklyn: Columbia Street - Halleck Street
703760f-a.text:
Columbia Street, south from Halleck Street to Gowanus Canal, showing
the New York State Canal Terminal Grain Elevator on the left.
August 31, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
